Certainly! Here's a catchy title for your travel story, formatted using HTML to make it visually appealing:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Prague: A Tale of Bridges, Castles, and Culinary Delights</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            color: #333;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #8B0000;
            font-size: 2.5em;
        }
        h2 {
            color: #2E8B57;
            font-size: 1.5em;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Prague: A Tale of Bridges, Castles, and Culinary Delights</h1>
    <h2>Exploring the Charm of Charles Bridge, Old Town & Karlstejn</h2>
</body>
</html>
```

This title captures the essence of your trip and highlights the key experiences you had in Prague. You can use this HTML code as a starting point for your travel story's webpage.
